The paper discusses the problem of Fourier phase retrieval, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields in computer science. However, based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the problem of recovering a signal from its phaseless Fourier transform measurements is a classic problem in signal processing and information theory. The paper also mentions multidimensional signals, which suggests that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SP (Signal Processing).
